<task id="postman-settingUpWorkspace">
    <title>Creating a Postman Collection</title>
    <taskbody>
        <prereq>
            <p><b>Prerequisites:</b></p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Install Postman desktop application.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Sign in to Postman account.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Create a Postman workspace.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </prereq>
        <context>
            <p>A collection in Postman is a set of API requests that can be configured for testing
                purposes. This task describes how to create a Postman collection using the <b>REST
                    API basics</b> template.</p>
            <p>To create a collection follow these steps:</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select <b>Collections</b> in the sidebar, then select <b>+ > REST API
                        basics</b>.</cmd>
                <info><p><image href="../images/pm-restApiBasicsSelect.png"/></p></info>
                <stepresult>A new collection will appear with pre-built <b>GET</b>, <b>POST</b>,
                        <b>PUT</b>, and <b>DELETE</b> request testers. <p><image
                            href="../images/pm-restApiBasics.png"/></p></stepresult>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Rename the collection using your REST API resource name. To rename your
                    collection, open the drop-down menu and select <b>Rename</b>. </cmd>
                <info>
                    <p><image href="../images/pm-collection-rename.png"/></p>
                    <p>This example uses the xmen resource from My REST API.</p>
                    <p><image href="../images/pm-collection-rename2.png"/></p>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Configure and run tests accordingly.</cmd>
                </step>
        </steps><postreq><p><ph conkeyref = "gen/related-links-leadin"/></p><ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <xref href="postman-testingGetRequest.dita"/>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
